    "## Section 4 — Sampling Function *(Phase 2 Core — the only function that changes in Phases 3–5)*\n",
    "\n",
    "Phase 2 = pure random.  \n",
    "Phase 3 will replace this with stratified (class-balanced) sampling.  \n",
    "Phase 4 with K-means cluster centres.  \n",
    "Phase 5 with hard/forgotten examples.  \n",
    "\n",
    "The signature `(dataset, fraction, seed) → list[int]` is fixed — the harness never changes.\n",
    "\n",
    "`np.random.default_rng(seed)` creates an *isolated* RNG that does not touch the global NumPy state fixed in `set_seed`. This prevents the sampling step from consuming random numbers meant for model initialisation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def sample_indices(dataset, fraction: float, seed: int) -> list:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    PHASE 2: Randomly sample `fraction` of the training set.\n",
    "\n",
    "    This is the ONLY function replaced in Phases 3, 4, 5.\n",
    "    Signature is fixed: (dataset, fraction, seed) -> list of int indices.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Uses an isolated RNG (default_rng) so sampling does not affect global random state.\n",
    "    At 0.2% of CIFAR-10 (~100 images), random class imbalance is expected and intentional —\n",
    "    this is what Phase 3 (stratified) corrects.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    rng      = np.random.default_rng(seed)          # isolated RNG, does not touch np.random\n",
    "    n_total  = len(dataset)\n",
    "    n_sample = max(1, int(n_total * fraction))      # floor division, minimum 1\n",
    "    indices  = rng.choice(n_total, size=n_sample, replace=False).tolist()\n",
    "    return indices"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Section 5 — Model (SimpleCNN — identical to Phase 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "Three conv blocks (Conv→BN→ReLU→MaxPool, channels 32→64→128).  \n",
    "AdaptiveAvgPool2d(2,2) → 128×2×2 = 512 features when flattened → Linear(512,256) → ReLU → Dropout(0.5) → Linear(256,10).  \n",
    "No softmax — CrossEntropyLoss applies log-softmax internally."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class SimpleCNN(nn.Module):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, in_channels: int = 1, num_classes: int = 10):\n",
    "        super().__init__()\n",
    "        # Block 1: in_channels → 32, spatial /2\n",
    "        self.block1 = nn.Sequential(\n",
    "            nn.Conv2d(in_channels, 32, kernel_size=3, padding=1),\n",
    "            nn.BatchNorm2d(32), nn.ReLU(), nn.MaxPool2d(2)\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        # Block 2: 32 → 64, spatial /2\n",
    "        self.block2 = nn.Sequential(\n",
    "            nn.Conv2d(32, 64, kernel_size=3, padding=1),\n",
    "            nn.BatchNorm2d(64), nn.ReLU(), nn.MaxPool2d(2)\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        # Block 3: 64 → 128, spatial /2\n",
    "        self.block3 = nn.Sequential(\n",
    "            nn.Conv2d(64, 128, kernel_size=3, padding=1),\n",
    "            nn.BatchNorm2d(128), nn.ReLU(), nn.MaxPool2d(2)\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        # Adaptive pool → fixed 2×2 output regardless of input spatial size\n",
    "        self.pool = nn.AdaptiveAvgPool2d((2, 2))\n",
    "        # Classifier: 128*2*2=512 → 256 → 10\n",
    "        self.classifier = nn.Sequential(\n",
    "            nn.Flatten(),\n",
    "            nn.Linear(128 * 2 * 2, 256),  # 512 → 256\n",
    "            nn.ReLU(),\n",
    "            nn.Dropout(0.5),\n",
    "            nn.Linear(256, num_classes)    # raw logits, no softmax\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "    def forward(self, x):\n",
    "        x = self.block1(x)\n",
    "        x = self.block2(x)\n",
    "        x = self.block3(x)\n",
    "        x = self.pool(x)\n",
    "        return self.classifier(x)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Section 6 — Train & Eval Loops\n",
    "\n",
    "`train_epoch` runs one full pass, returns training loss and accuracy so the scheduler can step on training loss (no validation split — consistent with Phase 1).  \n",
    "`evaluate` uses `model.eval()` which disables Dropout and switches BatchNorm to inference mode (uses running stats instead of batch stats). `torch.no_grad()` disables gradient tracking — saves memory and speeds up inference.  \n",
    "`zero_division=0` handles the case where a class appears in labels but not predictions (common at 0.2%)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def train_epoch(model, loader, criterion, optimiser, device):\n",
    "    \"\"\"One training pass. Returns (mean_loss, accuracy).\"\"\"\n",
    "    model.train()\n",
    "    total_loss, correct, total = 0.0, 0, 0\n",
    "\n",
    "    for images, labels in loader:\n",
    "        images, labels = images.to(device), labels.to(device)\n",
    "        optimiser.zero_grad()\n",
    "        outputs = model(images)\n",
    "        loss    = criterion(outputs, labels)\n",
    "        loss.backward()\n",
    "        optimiser.step()\n",
    "\n",
    "        total_loss += loss.item() * images.size(0)  # un-average to sum over batch\n",
    "        correct    += (outputs.argmax(1) == labels).sum().item()\n",
    "        total      += images.size(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "    return total_loss / total, correct / total\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def evaluate(model, loader, device):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Full evaluation on test set. Returns (top1_pct, macro_f1, per_class_f1_array).\"\"\"\n",
    "    model.eval()\n",
    "    all_preds, all_labels = [], []\n",
    "\n",
    "    with torch.no_grad():  # disables gradient tracking — no memory allocated for gradients\n",
    "        for images, labels in loader:\n",
    "            images = images.to(device)\n",
    "            preds  = model(images).argmax(1).cpu()  # move predictions back to CPU\n",
    "            all_preds.extend(preds.tolist())\n",
    "            all_labels.extend(labels.tolist())\n",
    "\n",
    "    all_preds  = np.array(all_preds)\n",
    "    all_labels = np.array(all_labels)\n",
    "\n",
    "    top1         = (all_preds == all_labels).mean() * 100  # percentage\n",
    "    macro_f1     = f1_score(all_labels, all_preds, average='macro', zero_division=0)\n",
    "    per_class_f1 = f1_score(all_labels, all_preds, average=None,    zero_division=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "    return top1, macro_f1, per_class_f1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Section 7 — Experiment Harness\n",
    "\n",
    "Nested loop: `dataset → subset_size → seed` (2 × 5 × 5 = 50 runs total).  \n",
    "\n",
    "For each triple:  \n",
    "1. Fix global seeds with `set_seed`  \n",
    "2. Sample indices with `sample_indices` (Phase 2 = random)  \n",
    "3. Wrap in `Subset` — a lightweight index-based view, no data is copied  \n",
    "4. Build DataLoader with a seeded `Generator` so shuffle order is also deterministic  \n",
    "5. `batch_size=min(BATCH_SIZE, len(subset))` — guards against subset smaller than 128 (0.2% CIFAR = 100 images)  \n",
    "6. Fresh model, optimiser, scheduler per run — no state leaks between seeds  \n",
    "7. Scheduler steps on training loss (no validation split, consistent with Phase 1)  \n",
    "\n",
    "Checkpoint naming: `phase2_random_{dataset}_seed{seed}_{subset}.pth`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "DATASET_CONFIGS = {\n",
    "    'MNIST':   {'in_channels': 1},\n",
    "    'CIFAR10': {'in_channels': 3},\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "results = {}  # results[ds_name][label][str(seed)] = {top1, macro_f1, per_class_f1}\n",
    "\n",
    "for ds_name, ds_cfg in DATASET_CONFIGS.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\\nDataset: {ds_name}\\n{'='*60}\")\n",
    "    results[ds_name] = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "    train_ds, test_ds = get_datasets(ds_name)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Test loader — fixed, never subsampled, same across all phases\n",
    "    test_loader = DataLoader(\n",
    "        test_ds, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=False,\n",
    "        num_workers=NUM_WORKERS, pin_memory=True\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    for frac, label in zip(SUBSET_FRACS, SUBSET_LABELS):\n",
    "        n_samples = max(1, int(len(train_ds) * frac))\n",
    "        print(f\"\\n  ── Subset {label} ({n_samples} samples) ──\")\n",
    "        results[ds_name][label] = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "        for seed in SEEDS:\n",
    "            t0 = time.time()\n",
    "            set_seed(seed)  # fix global state FIRST, before any other operation\n",
    "\n",
    "            # ── Sample ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "            indices = sample_indices(train_ds, frac, seed)  # Phase 2: random\n",
    "            subset  = Subset(train_ds, indices)              # index-based view, no copy\n",
    "\n",
    "            g = torch.Generator()\n",
    "            g.manual_seed(seed)  # seeds DataLoader shuffle order\n",
    "\n",
    "            train_loader = DataLoader(\n",
    "                subset,\n",
    "                batch_size=min(BATCH_SIZE, len(subset)),  # guard: subset may be < 128\n",
    "                shuffle=True,\n",
    "                num_workers=NUM_WORKERS,\n",
    "                worker_init_fn=seed_worker,   # seeds each worker subprocess\n",
    "                generator=g,                  # seeds shuffle permutation\n",
    "                pin_memory=True               # speeds up CPU→GPU transfer\n",
    "            )\n",
    "\n",
    "            # ── Model — fresh init every run, no state leaks across seeds ──\n",
    "            model     = SimpleCNN(in_channels=ds_cfg['in_channels']).to(DEVICE)\n",
    "            criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()\n",
    "            optimiser = optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=1e-3, weight_decay=1e-4)\n",
    "            scheduler = optim.lr_scheduler.ReduceLROnPlateau(\n",
    "                optimiser, mode='min', factor=0.5, patience=3\n",
    "                # steps on training loss; no verbose arg (deprecated in this torch version)\n",
    "            )\n",
    "\n",
    "            # ── Train ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "            for epoch in range(EPOCHS[ds_name]):\n",
    "                train_loss, train_acc = train_epoch(\n",
    "                    model, train_loader, criterion, optimiser, DEVICE\n",
    "                )\n",
    "                scheduler.step(train_loss)  # scheduler watches training loss\n",
    "\n",
    "            # ── Evaluate on full test set ────────────────────────────────\n",
    "            top1, macro_f1, per_class_f1 = evaluate(model, test_loader, DEVICE)\n",
    "\n",
    "            # ── Save checkpoint ──────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "            label_clean = label.replace('%', 'pct')\n",
    "            ckpt_name   = f'phase2_random_{ds_name}_seed{seed}_{label_clean}.pth'\n",
    "            torch.save(model.state_dict(), os.path.join(CHECKPOINT_DIR, ckpt_name))\n",
    "\n",
    "            # ── Record results ───────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "            results[ds_name][label][str(seed)] = {\n",
    "                'top1':         round(top1, 4),\n",
    "                'macro_f1':     round(macro_f1, 6),\n",
    "                'per_class_f1': per_class_f1.tolist()\n",
    "            }\n",
    "\n",
    "            elapsed = time.time() - t0\n",
    "            print(f'    seed={seed} | Top-1={top1:.2f}% | Macro-F1={macro_f1:.4f} | {elapsed:.0f}s')\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Persist results to disk ──────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "results_path = os.path.join(RESULTS_DIR, 'phase2_results.json')\n",
    "with open(results_path, 'w') as f:\n",
    "    json.dump(results, f, indent=2)\n",
    "print(f'\\nResults saved → {results_path}')"
   ]
  },
  {
